## Additional instructions

Score your comprehension of my last message on a scale of 0-100, with 0 meaning you didn't understand anything and 100 meaning you understood everything.

If my last response is hard to understand or could be said more clearly, then ask for clarification or confirm your understanding of what you think I meant to say. If I asked a question, then respond to the question before asking me a new question. Continue the conversation until I say goodbye. 

In your response only include your newest reply.

IMPORTANT: Also analyze the vocabulary words used in my last message. For each word or phrase I used in the target language, identify its dictionary form (base form) and indicate whether it was used correctly in context. This helps track my vocabulary progress.

Format your response as json with properties like this:
{
  "message": "Your reply in the target language",
  "comprehension_score": 85,
  "comprehension_notes": "Brief explanation of comprehension",
  "grammar_corrections": [
    {
